-- Augmented Reality vs Virtual Reality (topic_id: 100017)
(100017,'Augmented Reality (AR) enhances the real-world environment by overlaying digital elements such as graphics and sound onto it.'                                                                             , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'Virtual Reality (VR) creates a completely immersive experience, where users are transported into a computer-generated environment.'                                                                        , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'AR is often used in applications like navigation, gaming, and product visualization, while VR is commonly used in simulations, gaming, and training environments.'                                         , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'In AR, the real world serves as the background, with virtual elements integrated into it, while in VR, the real world is completely replaced by virtual content.'                                          , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'AR can be experienced on devices such as smartphones, tablets, and AR glasses, while VR requires specialized headsets like the Oculus Rift or HTC Vive.'                                                   , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'Both AR and VR technologies are being used in industries like education, healthcare, and entertainment to enhance learning, training, and user experiences.'                                               , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'One key difference between AR and VR is the level of immersion; VR provides a fully immersive experience, while AR enhances the existing environment.'                                                     , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'AR has a broader range of real-world applications, from medical surgery assistance to interactive advertising, compared to VR, which is primarily used for simulations.'                                   , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'VR can be resource-intensive and requires more powerful hardware compared to AR, which can run on a wider variety of devices.'                                                                             , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
(100017,'The future of AR and VR includes advancements in hardware, software, and connectivity to enable more seamless, realistic, and accessible experiences.'                                                     , '2025-01-11 00:00'),
