-- GraphQL vs REST (topic_id: 100023)
(100023,'GraphQL is a query language for APIs that allows clients to request exactly the data they need and nothing more.'                                                                                          , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'Unlike REST, which typically exposes multiple endpoints for different resources, GraphQL exposes a single endpoint for all data queries and mutations.'                                                    , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'GraphQL allows clients to specify the shape of the response data, enabling more efficient use of bandwidth by avoiding over-fetching or under-fetching of data.'                                           , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'REST APIs are based on fixed endpoints, while GraphQL offers a flexible schema that can evolve over time without breaking existing queries.'                                                               , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'One advantage of GraphQL over REST is that it allows clients to combine multiple resource queries into a single request, reducing the number of round trips to the server.'                                , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'REST APIs typically require multiple requests for related resources, while GraphQL allows fetching related data in a single request using nested queries.'                                                 , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'GraphQL supports real-time updates through subscriptions, allowing clients to receive new data automatically when the server state changes.'                                                               , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'REST APIs are simpler to implement, while GraphQL requires more upfront configuration for schema definition and query resolution.'                                                                         , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'GraphQL offers better flexibility for clients, but it can also lead to over-complication for small projects or simple APIs.'                                                                               , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
(100023,'The choice between GraphQL and REST depends on the complexity of the data needs, scalability requirements, and ease of development.'                                                                       , '2025-01-12 00:00'),
