-- Scrum Framework Explained (topic_id: 100029)
(100029,'Scrum is an Agile framework used to manage and complete complex projects, particularly in software development.'                                                                                           , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'In Scrum, work is organized into sprints, which are fixed-length iterations that typically last between 1 and 4 weeks.'                                                                                    , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'Scrum teams consist of a Scrum Master, a Product Owner, and the Development Team, each with distinct roles and responsibilities.'                                                                          , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'The Scrum Master facilitates the Scrum process, ensuring that the team follows Scrum practices and removes any obstacles to progress.'                                                                     , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'The Product Owner defines the product backlog, which contains a prioritized list of features, enhancements, and bug fixes to be completed during the project.'                                             , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'The Development Team is responsible for delivering working software at the end of each sprint, based on the items in the product backlog.'                                                                 , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'Scrum emphasizes collaboration, transparency, and delivering value to customers by focusing on the most important work first.'                                                                             , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'Daily stand-up meetings, sprint reviews, and sprint retrospectives are essential parts of the Scrum process, enabling teams to inspect and adapt their work regularly.'                                    , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'Scrum aims to create a collaborative environment where teams can respond quickly to changing requirements and deliver high-quality software.'                                                              , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
(100029,'The Scrum framework is widely adopted in software development but can be applied to other industries as well to manage complex projects.'                                                                  , '2025-01-13 00:00'),
