-- Clean Code Principles (topic_id: 100032)
(100032,'Clean Code refers to writing code that is easy to read, understand, and modify, adhering to principles that improve software quality.'                                                                     , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'One key principle of Clean Code is writing small functions that perform a single task, making code easier to test and debug.'                                                                              , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'Another principle is naming variables and functions descriptively, which improves code readability and helps others understand the code faster.'                                                           , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'Clean Code suggests using comments sparingly and only when necessary, as code should be self-explanatory through clear naming and good structure.'                                                         , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'It encourages writing code that is simple, avoiding unnecessary complexity, which makes maintenance easier and reduces the potential for errors.'                                                          , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'Clean Code advises avoiding duplication in code, instead promoting reusable and modular code to reduce maintenance efforts.'                                                                               , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'Refactoring is an essential practice in Clean Code, as it helps improve code structure over time without changing its external behavior.'                                                                  , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'Clean Code emphasizes the importance of handling errors gracefully and using exceptions appropriately to ensure code robustness.'                                                                          , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'It advocates for writing unit tests to ensure code correctness and to safeguard against future regressions.'                                                                                               , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100032,'Clean Code also promotes using meaningful abstractions, which allow developers to work with code at a higher level of understanding and reduce cognitive load.'                                            , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
