-- SQL vs NoSQL Databases (topic_id: 100034)
(100034,'SQL databases are relational, meaning they use structured query language (SQL) for defining and manipulating data.'                                                                                        , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'NoSQL databases are non-relational, offering flexibility for handling various data types, such as document, key-value, graph, and column-family stores.'                                                   , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'SQL databases are well-suited for complex queries and transactions with ACID compliance, ensuring data integrity.'                                                                                         , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'NoSQL databases are typically used for large-scale, distributed systems, offering horizontal scaling and high availability.'                                                                               , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'SQL databases are ideal for applications that require structured data and strong consistency, such as banking systems.'                                                                                    , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'NoSQL databases are preferred in applications with rapidly changing data and large-scale data storage, such as social media platforms.'                                                                    , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'The key difference lies in schema design: SQL databases have a fixed schema, while NoSQL databases allow dynamic schema creation.'                                                                         , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'NoSQL databases tend to favor eventual consistency over strict ACID compliance, allowing for higher availability in distributed systems.'                                                                  , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'SQL databases are usually vertically scalable, while NoSQL databases are horizontally scalable, making them better suited for cloud-native applications.'                                                  , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100034,'Choosing between SQL and NoSQL depends on use case, with SQL being more suitable for complex relational data and NoSQL for flexible, unstructured data.'                                                   , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
