-- Data Warehousing Concepts (topic_id: 100035)
(100035,'Data warehousing involves collecting, storing, and analyzing large volumes of data from multiple sources for business intelligence purposes.'                                                              , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'A data warehouse is typically designed for query and reporting rather than transactional processing, providing insights from historical data.'                                                             , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes are used to move data from operational systems into the data warehouse for analysis.'                                                                             , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'The data warehouse schema often includes a star or snowflake model to organize data in fact and dimension tables.'                                                                                         , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'Data warehouses support decision-making by providing a consolidated view of an organizations data, improving reporting and business analytics.'                                                           , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'OLAP (Online Analytical Processing) cubes are used in data warehouses to perform complex queries on large datasets in real time.'                                                                          , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'Data marts are subsets of data warehouses, focused on specific business areas or departments, improving performance and relevance.'                                                                        , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'Data quality and consistency are critical in data warehousing to ensure accurate reporting and analysis.'                                                                                                  , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
(100035,'Data governance ensures that the data in the warehouse complies with standards for quality, privacy, and security.'                                                                                        , '2025-01-14 00:00'),
