-- Functional Programming Basics (topic_id: 100036)
(100036,'Functional programming is a paradigm that treats computation as the evaluation of mathematical functions and avoids changing state and mutable data.'                                                      , '2025-01-15 00:00'),
(100036,'Functions in functional programming are first-class citizens, meaning they can be passed as arguments, returned from other functions, and assigned to variables.'                                          , '2025-01-15 00:00'),
(100036,'Pure functions are a key concept in functional programming, as they always produce the same output for the same input and have no side effects.'                                                           , '2025-01-15 00:00'),
(100036,'Immutability is another important concept in functional programming, where data cannot be changed once it is created.'                                                                                     , '2025-01-15 00:00'),
(100036,'Higher-order functions take other functions as arguments or return them as results, enabling powerful abstractions in functional programming.'                                                             , '2025-01-15 00:00'),
